00:11:57.270 --> 00:12:01.730
many multiples of this, but the British public weren’t buying it.

00:12:02.920 --> 00:12:08.690
The newspapers started referring to him as “Airmiles Andy”, and would

00:12:08.690 --> 00:12:13.570
report on stories of how he would insist on flying first class, sometimes

00:12:13.790 --> 00:12:18.880
even in British military planes, instead of going by car or by train.

00:12:20.250 --> 00:12:26.450
In the 1980s the British public might have laughed at this young prince being photographed with

00:12:26.450 --> 00:12:32.750
a different aristocratic girl every month, and falling out of fashionable nightclubs, and he

00:12:32.750 --> 00:12:38.130
certainly still had some public goodwill stored up after serving in the navy in the Falklands War.

00:12:39.280 --> 00:12:45.230
But fast forward 30 years, he was a divorced 50-year-old man who was seen

00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:50.560
to be a drain on the public purse and an embarrassment to British interests.

00:12:51.910 --> 00:12:56.600
And in 2010, he was photographed walking in Central Park with

00:12:56.610 --> 00:13:00.680
Jeffrey Epstein, who had been released the previous year from prison.

00:13:02.040 --> 00:13:08.460
Now, at this point the true extent of Epstein’s crimes and depravity weren’t publicly

00:13:08.460 --> 00:13:15.040
known, but he had been sent to prison for having sex with an underage girl, so he was

00:13:15.040 --> 00:13:19.790
certainly not the sort of person that the queen’s son should be photographed chatting with.

00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:29.190
And things went from bad to worse a year later when his ex-wife, Sarah Ferguson, admitted

00:13:29.430 --> 00:13:36.880
that Epstein had helped pay off her debts to the tune of £15,000, so around €20,000.

00:13:37.930 --> 00:13:43.570
Why was a convicted sex offender paying all of this money to the queen’s

00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:47.780
former daughter in law, to the mother of the queen’s grandchildren?

00:13:49.070 --> 00:13:56.750
Something smelled rotten, and in July of 2011 Prince Andrew was sacked, or forced to

00:13:56.750 --> 00:14:03.300
give up his role as special trade envoy, and he reportedly cut off all ties with Epstein.

00:14:04.700 --> 00:14:11.930
And since that fateful BBC interview in November of 2019, Prince Andrew has been truly

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:17.760
cast out, not allowed to speak publicly out of a fear that he further incriminates himself.

00:14:19.150 --> 00:14:25.120
There is, of course, the very real possibility that he might face criminal charges.

00:14:26.560 --> 00:14:32.990
He is not just accused of having sex with an underage girl who was a victim of trafficking, but of

00:14:32.990 --> 00:14:40.340
knowing full well what his friend Jeffrey Epstein was up to, and being a willing participant in it.

00:14:41.590 --> 00:14:49.345
If this is true, and his excuses don’t exactly inspire confidence that it isn’t, this is a

00:14:49.420 --> 00:14:55.869
serious crime, one for which regular members of the public would face some serious jail time.

00:14:57.439 --> 00:14:59.599
So, what comes next?

00:15:00.879 --> 00:15:05.559
